#: ../../A/all-your-base-are-belong-to-us.rst:5
msgid "all your base are belong to us"
msgstr "all your base are belong to us"

#: ../../A/all-your-base-are-belong-to-us.rst:7
msgid ""
"A declaration of victory or superiority. The phrase stems from a 1991 "
"adaptation of Toaplan's \"Zero Wing\" shoot-'em-up arcade game for the Sega "
"Genesis game console. A brief introduction was added to the opening screen, "
"and it has what many consider to be the worst Japanese-to-English "
"translation in video game history. The introduction shows the bridge of a "
"starship in chaos as a Borg-like figure named CATS materializes and says, "
"\"How are you gentlemen!! All your base are belong to us.\" [sic] In 2001, "
"this amusing mistranslation spread virally through the Internet, bringing "
"with it a slew of JPEGs and a movie of hacked photographs, each showing a "
"street sign, store front, package label, etc. hacked to read \"All your base"
" are belong to us\" or one of the other many supremely dopey lines from the "
"game (such as \"Somebody set up usthe bomb!!!\" or \"What happen?\"). When "
"these phrases are used properly, the overall effect is both screamingly "
"funny and somewhat chilling, reminiscent of the B movie \"They Live\"."
msgstr ""
"勝利あるいは優位の宣言。この語句は、Toaplanのシューティングアーケードゲーム「Zero Wing」を1991年にSega "
"Genesis(メガドライブ)ゲーム機向けに移植したものに由来する。オープニング画面に短い導入が追加されたのだが、これには多くの人がビデオゲーム史上最悪と考える日本語から英語への翻訳が含まれていた。導入では、CATSという名のボーグ風の人物が現れて「How"
" are you gentlemen!! All your base are belong to "
"us.」[原文ママ]と言う中、宇宙船のブリッジが混乱に陥る様子が映し出される。2001年、この愉快な誤訳がインターネットを通じてウイルスのように広まり、それとともに大量のJPEG画像と、改変写真の動画——道路標識、店先、商品ラベルなどが「All"
" your base are belong to us」やゲーム中の他の数々の極めて間抜けな台詞(「Somebody set up us the "
"bomb!!!」や「What "
"happen?」など)に書き換えられたもの——が出回った。これらの語句が適切に使われると、全体としての効果は、笑い転げるほど面白くも、どこか薄ら寒く、B級映画「They"
" Live」を思わせるものになる。"

#: ../../A/all-your-base-are-belong-to-us.rst:17
msgid ""
"The original has been generalized to \"All your X are belong to us\", where "
"X is filled in to connote a sinister takeover of some sort. Thus, \"When Joe"
" signed up for his new job at Yoyodyne, he had to sign a draconian NDA. It "
"basically said: All your code are belong to us.\" Has many of the "
"connotations of \"Resistance is futile; you will be assimilated\" (see "
":ref:`Borg`\\). Considered silly, and most likely to be used by the type of "
"person that finds :ref:`Jeff-K-` hilarious."
msgstr ""
"オリジナルは「All your X are belong to "
"us」へと一般化された。Xには何らかの不吉な乗っ取りを連想させる語が入る。たとえば「JoeがYoyodyneの新しい仕事に応募したとき、彼は過酷なNDAに署名しなければならなかった。要するにこう書いてあった。All"
" your code are belong to us(お前のコードはすべて我々のものだ)」。「Resistance is futile; you "
"will be assimilated(抵抗は無意味だ。お前は同化される)」(\\ :ref:`Borg`\\ "
"を参照)と多くの含意を共有する。ばかげているとみなされており、\\ :ref:`Jeff-K-`\\ を爆笑ものだと思うような手合いに使われやすい。"
